7","1213":"1213","1268":"1268","1235":"1235","1245":"1245","30 May 1281":"30 May 1281","about 1268":"about 1268","1307":"1307","Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England":"Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Foliot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Italian (Lombardy): variant of   Foglio  . This surname is very rare in Italy."],"variants":[{"name":"Foglio","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carmine, Dino, Flavio, Julieta, Sal, Salvatore.","Italian: probably from the Latin personal name <i>Folius</i> (which is embodied in the common placename Fogliano)."]}]},{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Foliot was born about 1237, in Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Samson Foliot. She had at least 1 son with Henry de Tyeys. She died about May 1282, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"Abt 1237–Abt May 1282":"umbes 1237–umbes mai 1282","1237–1282":"1237–1282","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1235–1282":"1235–1282","1268–1307":"1268–1307","1213–1281":"1213–1281","Abt May 1282":"umbes mai 1282","Abt 1237":"umbes 1237","1285":"1285","1282":"1282","1281":"1281","1237":"1237","1213":"1213","1268":"1268","1235":"1235","1245":"1245","30 May 1281":"30. mai 1281","about 1268":"umbes 1268","1307":"1307","Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England":"Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1237–Abt May 1282":"noin 1237–noin toukokuu 1282","1237–1282":"1237–1282","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1235–1282":"1235–1282","1268–1307":"1268–1307","1213–1281":"1213–1281","Abt May 1282":"noin toukokuu 1282","Abt 1237":"noin 1237","1285":"1285","1282":"1282","1281":"1281","1237":"1237","1213":"1213","1268":"1268","1235":"1235","1245":"1245","30 May 1281":"30. toukokuuta 1281","about 1268":"noin 1268","1307":"1307","Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England":"Fritwell, Oxfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1237–Abt May 1282":"environ 1237–environ mai 1282","1237–1282":"1237–1282","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1235–1282":"1235–1282","1268–1307":"1268–1307","1213–1281":"1213–1281","Abt May 1282":"environ mai 1282","Abt 1237":